discussionParameters.discussionTitle: Should we have a welfare system to support the unemployed?
discussionParameters.discussionDescription: Let us hear your opinions on this

discussionComments.text: oh good lord. After the last one, this one will be a trainwreck I tell you.
Yes
That welfare should be a prison.  Free room and board :-)
I agree that you should have a welfare system
Great ... we all agree .. let's vote.  Prison for everyone!
If we have one, then we should use it aggressively. It would be the greater good
@Ursula prison is for crimes not unemployment
Yes we should have a welfare system but the people on it should work for free in that system until they get some other work.
But putting everyone in prison would mean that the society would lose its productivity

I mean, this is a really complicated topic to cover in only 30 minutes. I think that you should have some kind of welfare, but we should also make sure that people paying into it are able to get benefits when they need it, so its fair. Also, there are ...other ways people can earn additional money while they're on welfare to get a little ahead.
@Daisy I think not everyone but some?
Like they could come and clean public pavements or do whatever jobs need more people ...
that's not a bad idea Gary.
@Gary That is a great idea
if you think about it, they could do volunteer work (paid for by the welfare) and learn new skills at once.
@Mary, yes I am expecting some people needing to go in prison. Just not all as some of our interlocutors suggested
How is it volunteer work if they get paid?
Daisy, how could you lose productivity from the unemployed?  They're just sitting around doing nothing but spend my tax dollars on their meth.
prison isn't tied to welfare, you don't send people to prison because they are unemployed. Debters prisons were abolished centuries ago in most civilized countries.
It is not the law to have a job. It \*is\* the law to not commit crime. By not having welfare for the unemployed, you make them criminals if they need anything that costs money. And that is wrong
It should be a law though
its less about the law and its more about taking care of people. That should be the priority.
The problem with not supporting the unemployed is that this **will** end up back firing for the rest of us
Welfare is not 'volunteer' work, we could call it 'learn on the job'
The law exists to take care of people
We need to take care of people but people should take care of themselves
No one says not to support them but support them while the rest of the population also gets something in return
yes, Bobby .... debtor's prison was abolished ... by a bunch of communist hippy liberals.  Now we all have to pay for their lefty stupidity
The law exists to regulate people
ok, this whole volunteer thing misses some obvious cases, what about people who are unemployed because they cannot hold a job, including volunteer work. People with medical conditions for example?
@Bobby, yes we need to take care of people otherwise the system fails. Totally on board with you!
The law exists to regulate people for the greater good
The lefty stupidity does annoy me quite a bit too
I sure hope for your sake Ursula you never miss a mortgage payment, so you don't end up in your own idea of a debters prison.
The law exists to be bended for our best needs
Laws that do not support the greater good are bad laws
But having a productive work force is the greater good
If you can find loopholes in those laws that would be best
People don't need regulating.  The government needs to be regulated.  And the first regulation should be to stop letting the government take my money and give it lazy freeloaders.
Havin people off the streets is good for everyone, not just for them, but giving them a reason to get up each day is good for them (and for us if they also do something that helps us) - win win
@Gary, yes we can definitely "bend" bad laws by voting new ones
When the robots become smart enough to take all the jobs, do you think that it is good that their owners get all the money and you have none? Then to eat you will become a criminal
I mean, you can always work around bad laws, but you shouldn't have to. The system should work to help people who need it, and lots of people who need welfare aren't able to do even minor work.
I do agree that my hard-earned money should not be given away to people who are not taking the effort to work
what if they can't Mary?
Exactly Bobby, so get the welfare people the income they need to survive but get them into jobs so they can work for us...I mean for that money already
If they have a disability, I am okay with it

Don't worry, Bobby.  You won't find me looking for handouts.  I take of myself and my family.  The world wold be a whole lot better if everyone did.  Maybe you should just run down your street throwing your money to all the unemployed bums.
What if they aren't hard working and make it off the backs of others? Laws must support the general good, not the good of the rich
Your money?? All money belongs to the state! Money is just an indication of how many services/products you can exchange with your government. It is essentially a government bond
If that is so, why should I bother to earn money anymore
Ursula, if you got injured on the job and weren't able to work, you ended up unemployed and debts to pay, how exactly are you going to provide?
Let the government pay me while I relax
Never mind putting the unemployed in prison.  We should put Daisy in there.  She wants to rob us all.
@Mary, so you can satisfy your needs, beyond what the state offers collectively
I think injuries should be covered and provided for just like disabilities
@Daisy - the state can have too much power too. Money is a good way of managing that. But the rules need to be just and fair
Hey Alex .... you should come over for a beer some time.  You sound like my kind of guy.
@Alex, I agree, otherwise the society won't be stable
But the thing is if the sick lame whoever need a hand up that's ok as long as we get some kickback out of that

ok, so basically we're talking Mary about classes of unemployed who merit having welfare right? People who don't have the ability to get a job, because of injury, or disability... can we agree those types of people should get assistance?
I'd like a beer. But not too many. Can't go driving drunk on the way home
There's people out there who can do stuff for us so we need to make the most of that, while still helping them
Yes Bobby I agree those should
I take that back, Alex ..... now you want rules that make everyone the same?  Life isn't fair.  I get mine, and you get yours.  And if you can't, then too bad.
But if you do not have any of that, you should not get anything from anyone
man, you guys are so cold blooded. Helping people doesn't just have to help your bottom line.
But it is important to look after your bottom line
You should see welfare as an investment: you get stability and higher productivity back!
I mean, if you want to look at like super overarching goals, then helping people is good for the economy, its good for the country, the world even.
I agree but only to an extent with Daisy

It cannot be a crime to be poor. There is no justice in that. If there is no legal way to meet the needs of yourself and your family, then the government, which \*represents\* the people, needs to provide these people with enough cash to not have to resort to crime
previousEdits: In cannot be a crime to be poor. There is no justice in that. If there is no legal way to meet the needs of yourself and your family, then the government, which \*represents\* the people, needs to provide these people with enough cash to not have to resort to crime

discussionComments.text: Hey, Gary.  You think the cheetah wants to help the baby gazelle?  Get real.  Life is tough, and if you can't survive it and pull your own weight, well I think Mr Darwin would say that it's best you get drained from the gene pool.
Yes Daisy is right, definitely as an investment but one that can pay off sooner than people realise if we set it up right
I am with Ursula on this one.
@Bobby, @Mary and @Alex I think we might be closer to an agreement?
Ursula, it sounds like you may just have it better off than others. Maybe you've never struggled in a position you'd need a help up like welfare.
@Ursual, the cheetah will help the gazelle if it means splitting up the baby lion
I do not believe in the "The strong have the responsibility to look after the weak" ideology
yeah, I think with the exception of Ursula.
Get a job, Alex.   The government isn't there to babysit everyone.
Mr. Pulled-Myself-Up-By-My-Bootstraps
I think we should take pride in pulling yourself up by your bootstraps
@Mary, it's not a responsibility, it's for our own benefit in the end
you know that expression comes from the fact that its impossible.

Ha ha, Gary.  Exactly right.  You take one end of the baby gazelle and I'll take the other and whichever one of us is stronger will get the whole thing, or the biggest part.  Just the way God wants it.
Daisy I can see that
oh don't bring "God" into this... \*rolls eyes\*
But it does not always end up like it
Are you not religious Bobby
It's not welfare to give lazy people money.  You do more harm than good.  If you can't get a job and pay your own way, then it's best if you just die.
Hmm maybe not I am vegetarian really LOL
definitely not, like I need another set of obnoxious rules made by old dead guys.
I still like Alex's Verdict, I think it covers what all of the non-sociopaths in the room agree on.
Rules are not that bad
So we agree that people should get welfare then?
I wonder what happens when Ursula gets older and can't support herself anymore? Does she think it just that she just crawl off somewhere?
but just that we need to set it up wisely, yes?
Only if they have injuries and disabilities
yes, but only if you legitimately cannot work
Nothing more nothing less
@Bobby, yes I voted for Alex's verdict too. Perhaps, the sociopaths in the room became that because they grew up without being told to make their beds?!
I mean, I'd add to that someone who is \*trying\* to find work as best they can. You shouldn't have them living in a trashcan while doing that.

Don't you worry about that.  I'll be able to look after myself for my entire life.  If I ever get to the point where I can't, then I'll just jump off a bridge.  Then you hippies can have a good cry about it.
@Mary, we need to define Injury and Disability too. Are you going to do that?
I think they did Daisy
I don't think anybody here would have a big cry over that Ursula, honestly it sounds like you need help... not like welfare, but like mental help.

Yes Bobby and Mary but we can use the people who can work for some jobs anyway so by making use of the people, steering them towards a job path, we can account for those who apply for welfare but don't really qualify (or should not really qualify) for it
I feel that someone else already must have and if not the system has been inaccurate all this time Alex
How about, we provide welfare to people willing to give back to the community and exile the rest? Say to Australia?
so if they are fit etc. then work them more
If you don't know what injury and disability are, then maybe you should drop out of this discussion.  You probably don't have enough intelligence to say anything useful.
Gary, I'm ok with that as long as its not exploiting them... the goal is to help them get back on their feet, not to just bleed them dry.
if they are not, then they can work less
previousEdits: if they are not, than they can work less

discussionComments.text: then
@Ursula, what if you can't get to that bridge any more? Do you want agency in your death or does it not matter? Your ability to control your destiny depends on the lines the State draws around that
I think that Alex needs a dictionary next to him
so, if everyone except for Ursula agrees for Alex's point we're stuck in here because he won't agree?
After all, you might be in jail for stealing a loaf of bread
Alex, I don't want any Death Agency.  Is that another Obama thing to take away freedom?
Ursula sucks.
Probably is
Freedom is not a right! It's only a privilege society bestows on us
If you are in jail for stealing food because you ran out of money, how will you do what you want?
That is not very nice Bobby
But they are unpleasant
Call any vote you want.  I'll support it just so that I don't have to listen to all you lefties any more.
I mean, he either is trolling us, or he legitimately believes people who are too injured or sick to work should just lay down and die. I don't know which one is more sad and pathetic.
I am not a lefty
So why don't you vote for my proposal then?
previousEdits: So why don't you vote for my proposal then?

discussionComments.text: its not really leftist to suggest sick people should not be left to die in a ditch. I mean, unless the window has shifted real real far.
How we build our laws to support the greater good in these sorts of difficult cases define who we are
I voted for Daisy yes just so Ursula can be exiled.

No, I am trying to have a proper conversation about this.  Welfare is for losers.  What is so hard to understand about that?  It is not fair and just to take money from winners and give it to losers.  Do you do that in poker?  Or Monopoly?
then vote for Daisy Ursula... that way you can go somewhere without welfare where you can be a "winner".
I am still not okay with the "unsick" people getting welfare
I think so too Ursula. It is my right to do what I wish with my money
Wait - we \*do\* redistribute money in monopoly! You are ok with that @Ursula? Or do you need to rewrite the rules of the game?
What are you talking about?  Money doesn't get redistributed in Monoply.  The winners take it from the losers through fair play.
Mary, then vote yes for Daisy
Yes, vote for this @Ursula. Fake it till you make it. We can slowly but surely reform you in the end
What are these rules you are playing with Alex?
I am totally lost now. What's going on here people?
I do not agree with jailing the people
look, we can all agree on Daisy's proposal right? its limited/beneficial to everyone welfare, and Usula gets to go live with the spiders where he belongs.
I do not know as well Gary
I do not think anyone should be exiled for wanting to keep their money
Try and keep up there, Gary.  It's not rocket science.

Testing the verdict here. Like if you support:

_** Welfare for people who deserve and are willing/likely to give back to the community. The rest and @Ursula will be exiled, say in Australia **_

pastedItems.item: Welfare for people who deserve and are willing/likely to give back to the community. The rest and @Ursula will be exiled, say in Australia

discussionComments.text: I'm fine with jailing the people that commit true crimes
common guys, vote for Daisy
I am okay with that too Alex

discussionVerdicts.text: It cannot be a crime to be poor. There is no justice in that. If there is no legal way to meet the needs of yourself and your family, then the government, which *represents* the people, needs to provide these people with enough cash to not have to resort to crime
Yes ok it can't be a crime to be poor but let's have the help set up in such a way that we can still make use of that workforce while they are on welfare
Welfare for people who deserve and are willing/likely to give back to the community. The rest and @Ursula will be exiled, say in Australia
